Canada Southern Petroleum Ltd said itsboard has authorized an offering of about three mln shares oflimited voting stock to shareholders of record on June 23.    The company said the rights offering will expire AugustThree.  The rights are nontransferable.    It said shareholders will be entitled to buy one new sharefor every three held at one dlr U.S. or 1.34 dlrs Canadian.Shareholders subscribing for their entire allotments will havethe option of subscribing for shares not bought by others on acontingent allotment basis in any amount up to 100 pct of theiroriginal allotments. Reuter&#3;